According to the principle of minimum potential energy, a system is in a stable equilibrium state when its potential energy reaches to a local minimum value. The stable equilibrium conditions can be described as7∂Uz1,z2,⋯,zn∂z1=∂Uz1,z2,⋯,zn∂z2=⋯=∂Uz1,z2,⋯,zn∂zn=0∂2Uz1,z2,⋯,zn∂zi2>0,i=1,2,⋯,n.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
